      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "flips = gets.chomp\npage = []\n\n7.times do\n  row = gets.chomp\n  page << row\nend\n\nflips.chars.map do |flip|\n  if flip == \"H\"\n    page.map!{|row| row.reverse.tr(\"XO\", \"OX\") }\n  elsif flip == \"V\"\n    page = page.reverse.map{|row| row.tr(\"XO\", \"OX\") }\n  else\n    # Rotate 180°\n    page = page.reverse.map{|row| row.reverse }\n  end\nend\n\nputs page",
      "statement": "You have a page that is 7x10 with an {{X}} marked on it. You perform some number of 'flips' on this page and want to see how the page looks after these flips.\n\nA <<horizontal flip>> {{H}} flips the page over left-to-right, and turns the {{X}} to an {{O}} (since it's now facing the other way).\n\nA <<vertical flip>> {{V}} flips the page over top-to-bottom, and turns the {{X}} to an {{O}} (since it's now facing the other way).\n\nA <<rotation>> {{R}} spins the page around by 180°, without changing the {{X}} (or {{O}}, if flipped already).\n\nGiven a string [[flips]] of {{V}}, {{H}} and {{R}} symbols, and the 7 lines of the page with an {{X}} marked somewhere on the page, print the final page after all of the flips.\n\n<<Note:>> a {{V}} or an {{H}} on a page that's already been flipped (by a {{V}} or an {{H}}) will turn the {{O}} back to an {{X}}.",
